propDescriptions.anchorEl: A HTML element, or a function that returns it. It's used to set the position of the menu.
propDescriptions.autoFocus: If true (Default) will focus the [role="menu"] if no focusable child is found. Disabled children are not focusable. If you set this prop to false focus will be placed on the parent modal container. This has severe accessibility implications and should only be considered if you manage focus otherwise.
propDescriptions.classes: Override or extend the styles applied to the component. See CSS API below for more details.
propDescriptions.disableAutoFocusItem: When opening the menu will not focus the active item but the [role="menu"] unless autoFocus is also set to false. Not using the default means not following WAI-ARIA authoring practices. Please be considerate about possible accessibility implications.
propDescriptions.onClose:
Callback fired when the component requests to be closed.

Signature:
function(event: object, reason: string) => void
event: The event source of the callback.
reason: Can be: "escapeKeyDown", "backdropClick", "tabKeyDown".
propDescriptions.sx: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details.
propDescriptions.transitionDuration: The length of the transition in ms, or 'auto'
propDescriptions.TransitionProps: Props applied to the transition element. By default, the element is based on this Transition component.
propDescriptions.variant: The variant to use. Use menu to prevent selected items from impacting the initial focus.

root.description: Styles applied to the root element.
